      "writtenOn": "2021-07-28T17:24:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just a guess, but I suspect plain old uint64_t is okay and gets translated to u64 everywhere. On the other hand, __u64 (and maybe __uint64_t?) is a typedef from a Linux header that ends up with the wrong type on 32-bit systems, but it is probably not used (directly) by libminijail.h.\n\nAll that said, I don\u0027t see any reason we couldn\u0027t just include a matching __u64 \u003d u64 line like the other __u* types, unless that leads to unused code warnings.",
